Bihar
Oct 11, 2014
Child Sexual Abuse, Rape, Sexual Harassment at Work
Description:
			A shocking incident of a minor girl allegedly being raped by her tutors for two months has come to light in Bihar's Nawada district, a police officer said today.

The 16-year-old girl has alleged that two tutors her coaching institute forcibly took her on their bike to a hideout when she was going for tutorial classes from her village Dohara under Maskaur police station area two months ago. They kept her in confinement and raped her, Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP) Sarful Rahman said.

The girl somehow managed to escape yesterday from her abductor's clutches and reached Hisua from where she called up police who rushed to her help and took her to Sadar hospital for medical examination where the rape was confirmed, the DSP said quoting a Sadar hospital doctor Neelam Kumari.

The girl has identified her rapists as Rahul Kumar and Amit Kumar, he said.

